# Claude Code local agent scratch
.claude/

# OneDrive / Google Drive restore duplicates — patterns like ".env(1).vault",
# "dist(2)/", ".claude(1)/" that cloud-sync tools create when they restore
# previously-deleted files. They always match "something (N)" or "something(N)".
*\ \(?\)*
*\(?\)*
*\ \(??\)*
*\(??\)*

# Private strategy / TODO / setup docs — live alongside the repo in
# SimpleITSRQ/private-notes/, never in git. If these patterns match a
# file in the working tree, they will be ignored on every commit.
USER-TODO.md
PASSIVE-INCOME-ROADMAP.md
CLOUDFLARE-ZERO-TRUST-SETUP.md
